column4: <content>[recto] Children's Games. Costume book, Veit Conrad Schwarz (1541-1587/88), of Augsburg in Braunschweig, Herzog Anton-Ulrich Mus.; referring to his childhood. The book deals with the years 1541-1561 ""...um 1550 kam ich widerzurüch zu meinen..."" Folios 11 and 12 referring to the years 1550 and 1551 (when V.C. Schwarz was 11-11 [sic] years) deal with Children's Games, f. 11 (summer); f. 12 (winter) [...] Repr. and discussed in: August FINK, Die Schwarzschen Trachtenbücher, Berlin [Deutscher Verein für Kunstwissenschaft], 1963, pp. 188-201; [verso] Max HERMANN, 'Bilder aus dem Kinderleben des sechzehnten Jahrhunderts', in: Mitteilungen der Gesellschaft für Deutsche Erziehungs- und Schulgeschichte, XX, Berlin 1910, pp. 125 with additional literature on children's games.</content>
